latestPosts.caption:
Unwinding 2024 with me.
I know I’m late to this, but maaannn… 2024 was my year. The most fun, the most growth, a year of risks, rewards, and so many moments that made me stop and think, Is this really my life?
I started the year fresh, literally. Moved into a new home on January 1st, hands down the best decision ever. Then came the big leaps. Left two jobs in six months (technically quit one in 2023). Up-skilled while working full-time, and it paid off. I learned new skills, became a digital nomad, graphic design and content creation started paying my bills. And oh, did I travel. Traveled across seven states, and a month-long staycation in Himachal.

Somewhere between the mountains and the stillness, I found adventure. Ziplined across Bhimtal, flying over the lake was pulse-racing. Rode a horse named Sultan through the hills, he was a charmer.

Growth isn’t always soft and dreamy. I gained weight, felt my body change, and realized age was catching up. Fitness became a priority, on and off, thanks to all the travel but from here on out, it’s non-negotiable.

Experienced the biggest heartbreak of my life… and it wasn’t from a man. Life is wild like that.

Somewhere in between it all, I found myself. Or at least, I started to. I stopped chasing perfection and started embracing growth. Accepted my flaws, my journey, my ever-evolving self. I realized that the work on yourself never really stops, it just deepens. And in the midst of all this self-discovery, I had the most surreal experience of all: kayaking at sunset, surrounded by golden skies and what seemed like endless water. For a moment, time stood still.

By the end of the year, I looked back and realized, I did it. Everything I planned for 2024? Manifested, worked for, and achieved. Success is personal, and to me, this year was everything. Big love to my small circle who held it down and dealt with my chaotic brain through all the transitions.

2024 was a trip, but 2025? Oh, it’s gonna be a year of pure magic incoming✨
